Twelve people were massacred by gunmen armed  with AK47 assault rifles in Tokoza black township east of here late Friday,  police said Saturday.
Police spokeswoman Janine Smith told the domestic news agency SAPA that  the gunmen stormed a house in the township and opened fire on the occupants at  7:30 p.m. (1730 GMT). The victims were aged between 13 and 25 years-old.
Smith said it appeared as if the youths had been staying in the house for  about a month and it was not known if they had been affiliated to any  political grouping.
